<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ChainedFixupTarget holds all the information about an external symbol</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// necessary to bind this binary to that symbol. These values are referenced</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// indirectly by chained fixup binds. This structure captures values from all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// import and symbol formats.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Be aware there are two notions of weak here:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   WeakImport == true</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     The associated bind may be set to 0 if this symbol is missing from its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     parent library. This is called a &quot;weak import.&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   LibOrdinal == BIND&#95;SPECIAL&#95;DYLIB&#95;WEAK&#95;LOOKUP</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     This symbol may be coalesced with other libraries vending the same</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     symbol. E.g., C++&#39;s &quot;operator new&quot;. This is called a &quot;weak bind.&quot;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MH&#95;DYLDLINK file. Fixups generally represent rebases and binds. Binds also</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   MachORebaseBindEntry   - for dyld opcode-based tables, including threaded-</span></CodeLine>
